# README — Oscillator Controller Modifications & Incident Report

## 1. Overview
This document summarizes:
- Code modifications
- Deployment procedure
- Incident description
- Hypotheses and questions

## 2. Code Modifications

### Removed Safety Checks
- StateStatusCheck
- BaseStateCheck

Reason: allow execution when robot is suspended.

### Initialization
- Added default pose targets
- Added CSV logging of joint states

### Advance Loop
- Logging inside control loop
- Reset handling
- GoToDefault initialization

### Oscillation Modes
- Sinus (0.1 Hz)
- Chirp (0.1 → 2 Hz over 20s)

### Motion Manager
- Only oscillate mode kept

## 3. Deployment Procedure
1. Power on robot
2. Connect via WiFi + SSH
3. Replace controller
4. Launch ANYmal Software
5. Suspend robot
6. Run oscillator in manual mode

## 4. Incident

Expected:
- Go to default pose
- Start oscillation

Observed:
- Immediate trembling
- No default pose reached
- Shutdown after ~3s

## 5. Differences vs Previous Run
- Added CSV logging
- Switched sinus → chirp

## 6. Hypotheses
- Logging breaks real-time loop
- Chirp too aggressive
- Safety checks removed
- Gains not adapted

## 7. Questions
- Is logging in control loop safe?
- Recommended limits for chirp?
- Safe gains?
- Cause of failsafe?

## 8. Debug Plan
- Remove logging
- Limit frequency
- Reduce gains
- Re-enable checks

## 9. Conclusion
Likely combination of timing + excitation + safety removal.